ch.unibas.informatik.hs15.cs203.datarepository.apps.cli

Enum Option

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Option>
      • ch.unibas.informatik.hs15.cs203.datarepository.apps.cli.Option
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Option>

     enum Option
extends Enum<Option>
    The Option enum represents available options for commands of this application. Options have an OPTION_MARKER which is an indicator that a given argument is an option name. Without this marker, options are not recognized as themselves. Usually options do have an argument, which is directly followed by the option name, but some options do not have an argument and are called 'flag' options. An example of an option with argument would be --description "The description" Do note the quotes of the text and the whitespace between the option's name (description) and its argument ("The description"). The option --verbose is a typical 'flag' option. Note: Option names are case insensitive
    Author:
    Loris

        Parameters:

      • parse

        public static Option parse(String str)
        Parses a given String to a matching Option. This is a case sensitive matching and the string may has the OPTION_MARKER or not. So verbose, VERBOSE, --verbose and --VERbose are all mapped to the VERBOSE. If there is no mapping found, null is returned. Use this method instead of java.lang.Enum.valueOf(Str)
        Parameters:
        str - The string to parse (If this is null, null is returned).
        Returns:
        Returns the matching Option or null if none is found.
